message: Focus on using 'growth serum' on basic ingredients initially to reach 'grown' (value ~5-10) or 'super-grown' (value ~10-15), but stop before 'ultra-grown' as it often leads to negative values. The most valuable items (up to 35) are created by combining two basic ingredients, and then applying 'growth serum' to that combined item once or twice. Combining a 'super-grown' item with a fresh basic ingredient also reliably increases value (to ~20-25). Remember, the previous player advised combining 'up to three' items; trying to combine four components consistently results in very negative values. Avoid using 'mutation catalyst' as it generally zeroes out or reduces item value.

message: Focus on the 'growth serum' tool! Small items (like bird, pufferfish, bee, butterfly, trout, lizard) consistently reach a value of 15 after 3 applications (grown, super-grown, ultra-grown). Medium items (snake, crab, squid) can also reach 15, but a third application can make them negative. Large items (elephant, lion, whale) are very risky with the serum, often turning negative after the second application. The 'mutation catalyst' consistently decreased item values in my experience, so use it with extreme caution. The highest scores come from combining multiple fully 'grown' items.
